        <div class="faq-answer"><p>PXP (Product Experience Platform) is the foundation — it unifies all product knowledge including descriptions, materials, care instructions, imagery, and translations. CXP (Customer Experience Platform) builds on PXP by capturing every customer interaction as a selling ceremony, storing associate feedback, and using that data to continuously refine the AI Agent's recommendations. Together they create a self-improving intelligence loop.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          How does the AI learn and improve over time?
          <span class="faq-icon"><i class="ti ti-plus"></i></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Every customer interaction is captured as a session in CXP. After each session, associates can provide feedback and corrections — strengthening the AI's understanding of your customers and products. This feedback loop means the AI gets more accurate with every interaction. The sooner you implement PXP, the faster the AI accumulates the knowledge it needs.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          Can the selling session continue after the customer leaves the store?
          <span class="faq-icon"><i class="ti ti-plus"></i></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Yes. When a customer leaves the store, the AI Agent carries the interaction forward. If the customer browses your website at home that evening, the AI can surface recommendations based on what they tried in-store, what the associate noted, and what's been wishlisted — keeping the experience personalized across channels.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          How does 121 Commerce relate to Teamwork Commerce Services (TCS)?
          <span class="faq-icon"><i class="ti ti-plus"></i></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>PXP and CXP are shared platform services within Teamwork Commerce Services — the same product and customer intelligence layers that power other apps across the platform. 121 Commerce is where they converge at the point of sale: real-time associate guidance, backed by the same PXP product data and CXP customer intelligence that TCS runs on. TAP's secure identity layer and TEAMMATE's associate access sit underneath the same experience.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-question" onclick="this.parentElement.classList.toggle('open')">
          How is 121 Commerce different from other retail AI solutions?
          <span class="faq-icon"><i class="ti ti-plus"></i></span>
        </button>
        <div class="faq-answer"><p>Most retail AI focuses on e-commerce recommendations or customer-facing chatbots. 121 Commerce is built for the associate — it's a co-pilot for the physical sales floor. It's natively integrated with Teamwork's POS, OMS, RFID, and inventory systems, so recommendations are backed by real-time stock data, customer history, and product intelligence. No other platform offers this depth of AI natively integrated with the full retail stack.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

